A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Primary and Secondary Education – Virtual Schools – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of requiring each county board of education to establish a virtual school;
4 providing a certain standard for the criteria for enrollment in a virtual school
5 established by the State Department of Education or a county board; providing that
6 a certain outreach campaign be conducted equitably; and generally relating to
7 virtual schools.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – Education
10 Section 7–1402(a) and 7–1403
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Education
16 7–1402.
17 (a) (1) (I) Except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection and
18 subject to the approval of the Department, a county board [may] SHALL establish one
19 virtual school for the elementary, middle, and high school grade bands.
20 (II) A COUNTY BOARD THAT DETERMINES THAT IT IS UNABLE TO
21 OFFER A VIRTUAL SCHOOL TO STUDENTS IN THE COUNTY ON ITS OWN IS
22 ENCOURAGED TO COLLABORATE WITH ONE OR MORE OTHER COUNTY BOARDS TO
23 JOINTLY ESTABLISH A VIRTUAL SCHOOL.
