1 diversity under subsection (e) of this section and any other criteria established by the
2 county board.
3 (e) To the extent practicable, the student body of a virtual school shall reflect the
4 socioeconomic, racial, ethnic, cultural, and gender diversity of the students enrolled in the
5 public school system in the county.
6 (f) (1) The county board shall develop an EQUITABLE outreach campaign to
7 provide information to the public on the availability of the virtual school option.
8 (2) The EQUITABLE outreach campaign shall be designed to encourage
9 applications from students who meet the intent of subsection (e) of this section, including
10 the production of materials and communications in languages spoken by more than the
11 percentage of the student population in the local school system determined appropriate by
12 the county board.
13 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
14 1, 2025.

